Is there any approach to get `depth`, `lineNumber` or `position` of current node in a real XML file?
As it's done using native `XmlTextReader`: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.xml.xmltextreader.lineposition?view=netcore-3.1
```csharp
while (reader.Read()){
       switch (reader.NodeType){
         case XmlNodeType.Element:
           Console.Write("{0} {1},{2}  ", reader.Depth, reader.LineNumber, reader.LinePosition);
           Console.WriteLine("<{0}>", reader.Name);
           break;
       }
    }
```

I have tried to get `Depth` of OpenXMLReader, but it seems that it is returning depth of element in some stack which is not real depth of current xml node.

It would be nice to have such functionality.
